creator: Pansy
description:
LibriVox recording of The Browns at Mt. Hermon by Pansy.
Read in English by BookAngel7

When she mistakenly receives an offer of work addressed only to "Mary Brown," the lonely young heiress Mary Thornton Brown forms an audacious plan--to spend her summer not as a guest at a fashionable resort but as a hired girl in Mrs. Roberts' boarding house. Over the course of her adventure, she meets people from many different walks of life, a number of them, to her amusement, sharing her own last name. A certain gentleman boarder is particularly pleasant--but even he is not the best friend Mary will meet during her summer at Mt. Hermon. - Summary by bookAngel7

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (163MB)

title: The Browns at Mt. Hermon

reviews.reviewbody: Trying to keep track of all the Mr. Browns (and Mary Browns) in this story is a fun little challenge. :) A very sweet story in harmony with the rest of Pansy's material. Mt Hermon is strongly reminiscent of early Chautauqua, with its tents and sessions and lectures. The reader does a wonderful job. Thanks for the recording!

Talk about preachy, this was less a story and more a sermon than anything!  If this is your genre, you will get more than you expect.  Not my type o hype tho.  

Reader was excellent, recording quality was excellent, just WAAAAAY too preachy.
